## 12. CONTRIBUTION TYPES IN DSR

"Contribution" must be specified, not merely claimed. The table below shows
the recognized types and what is needed to substantiate each:

| Contribution type | What it consists of | Substantiation required |
|---|---|---|
| New artifact | An artifact that does not previously exist | Evidence of gap; evaluation of the artifact |
| Improved artifact | Enhancement of an existing artifact | Documented deficiency in prior work; comparative evaluation |
| Context-specific adaptation | Transfer of existing artifact to new context | Justification for why adaptation is needed; evaluation in new context |
| Set of design principles | Generalizable rules derived from the design process | Explicit derivation from evaluation; theoretical grounding |
| Design theory (partial) | Abstract claims about design that go beyond a single artifact | Theoretical integration; multiple instantiations (rare in master's theses) |

---

## 13. COMMON ERRORS AND HOW TO AVOID THEM

| Error | Why it matters | Correction |
|---|---|---|
| DSR used as a label without applying its logic | Examiners recognize missing DSR structure | Address all six DSRM activities explicitly |
| No clearly defined artifact | Violates G1 | Define artifact type, name, and scope early |
| Evaluation conducted only once, at the end | Design Cycle is absent | Build formative evaluation into the design process |
| Evaluation reports only positive findings | Lacks credibility | Report negative findings; show how they influenced the design |
| Design decisions unjustified | Rigor Cycle is absent | Ground each decision in the knowledge base or requirements |
| Research gap asserted without derivation | Weak literature work | Derive the gap from critical comparison of related artifacts |
| Meta-requirements defined after design | Circular reasoning; invalidates the evaluation | Fix requirements before design begins |
| Design principles absent from discussion | Scientific contribution is unclear | Derive principles explicitly from the evaluation; justify each |
| Iterations not documented | Violates G6 | Include iteration log in appendix; summarize in main text |
| Kernel theories listed but not connected to design | Decoration without function | Show explicitly which design decision each theory informs |
| Artifact scope not defined | Contribution is unassessable | State the context, assumptions, and limits of applicability |

