## 14. DSR THESIS CHECKLIST

Use this list to evaluate completeness before submitting any chapter.

**Artifact and framing:**
- [ ] Artifact type is defined (construct, model, method, or instantiation)
- [ ] Artifact name and scope are clearly stated
- [ ] Context and applicability limits are specified

**DSR logic:**
- [ ] All three cycles (Relevance, Design, Rigor) are traceable in the thesis structure
- [ ] All six DSRM activities are addressed
- [ ] DSR is justified for this research question, not merely labeled
- [ ] Kernel theories are connected to specific design decisions

**Requirements and evaluation:**
- [ ] Meta-requirements and evaluation criteria are defined before design begins
- [ ] Evaluation method is appropriate for the artifact type
- [ ] Evaluators and context are described
- [ ] Negative findings are reported
- [ ] Evaluation results are linked back to the criteria from Chapter 3

**Iteration:**
- [ ] At least one evaluatively motivated revision is documented
- [ ] Each iteration includes: starting state, decisions, result, and findings
- [ ] Iteration boundaries and stopping rationale are stated

**Contribution:**
- [ ] Contribution type is explicitly identified
- [ ] Design principles are stated and derived from the evaluation
- [ ] Generalizability and limitations are addressed on all four levels
  (data, method, context, generalizability)

**Formal:**
- [ ] Core DSR references are included and used substantively
- [ ] All figures, tables, and appendix items are numbered and referenced
- [ ] Iteration documentation is available in the appendix
